im on vacation. i didnt think id be able to get online but i have been. and thought id update since i havent in kinda a while. im in newyork right now. i drove in newyork bitches..im all hardcore now. ill be home saturday right before the show. cape renewal, lucerin blue, and project 86...plus thr..how freakin awesome is that? hmm yeah really awesome. ive been thinking about deleting this journal. im not sure if i could do it though. we'll see. just always remember....

fireworks are overrated, just like everything else in this world. im not use to being home on the 4th. whatever. i leave for vacation tomorrow, and i'll be back saturday. oh yay *sarcastically*. its too loud from all the fireworks, and its kinda putting me in a bad mood. i need to NOT be here anymore.

i wish the sun would hide it's head so i could watch you dream some more.

lisa got paid today. hecks yah. but when i was driving home from martins..i was coming down adams road, and right where it crosses with fir, if you look down adams, it's kind of like a big hill. and i started thinking about how when i was in florida, when you're on your way to the beach, there was always a hill before you got there..and then you go up the hill and, bam, you see the ocean. like-its no where in sight and then all of a sudden you see this gorgeous thing in front of you. it's almost overwhelming. well anyways, i've lived here for 5 years and never noticed that adams looked like that. and it reminded me so much, too much, of florida. except, there were no palm trees on the the sides of the road. god, it kills me that i cant go outside and see palm trees whenever i want. i think i've lived here too long. one second i was happy, and the next second i was homesick and crying. 

i.hate.living.here.

im leaving for vacation monday, and the day we get back there's an honour recital show. double yay.

boy meets girl.
boy loves girl. 
girl pretends to love boy.
ooops....

that's what this song is about.


"I Always Told You I Was A Real Clumsy One"

Laying in my room.
Your picture's on my dresser.
Staring back at me.
I can try and remember the days when we'd lay on my couch, whispering sweet nothings, 
and looking at each other like there's tomorrow.
Except there is.
And I definately woke up too soon.
Can you remember?
Please tell me you don't remember....

Do do do, what I do to you.
Pretending.
I'm sorry to say that all it ever was....
All I ever did...
Was pretend.
Whoever said honesty was a necessity?
Only for you.
Only for you.

I can't say sorry enough times for what I did.
Not that I would.
Well, maybe I'd say it to you one more time if I thought you'd listen.
I know you won't.

You know the pain will ease someday.
And I know the scars are forever.
If I could take it back, 
Maybe I wouldn't have let you waste so much time on me.
Even though you'll say you didn't.

Do do do, what I do to you.
Pretending.
I'm sorry to say that all it ever was....
All I ever did...
Was pretend.
Whoever said honesty was a necessity?
Only for you.
Only for you.

It's too bad loving you was so hard for me,
And loving me was so easy for you.
Hopefully it doesn't hurt to bad when you dream about me.
Because I know you do.
You gave me the only key to your heart, 
And I lost it along the way.
I always told you I was a real clumsy one.
Trust me with nothing, please.
I do it all for me.
All for me.

Whoever said honesty was a necessity?
Only for you, baby.
Only for you.
